com.kuka.geometry.templates

Interface ISpatialObjectTemplate


  • public interface ISpatialObjectTemplate
    Represents an object template. The template can be used to instantiate one or more SpatialObjects and its subclasses VirtualObject, PhysicalObject and Tool.

    • Method Summary

      • createInstance

        <T extends SpatialObject> T createInstance(Class<T> clazz)
                                    throws TemplateException
        Like createInstance(), but with the additional requirement that the returned object match the given type.
        Type Parameters:
        T - the type of the desired template instance
        Parameters:
        clazz - the required Class the template instance must be equal to or derived from
        Returns:
        A new transient object of a dynamic type compatible with clazz, never null.
        Throws:
        TemplateClassException - if the template didn't match the expected type
        TemplateException - if the specified template is invalid

      • getInstanceClass

        Returns the Class associated with this template.
        Returns:
        The Class which instances of this template will have as class.
